<br>
I can hardly believe this ceremony happened, I dont want to. It's like the kids were being treated like good little  pets, or toddlers who aren't capable of achieving anything on their own merits. What an incredible insult. I can hardly imagine a worse way to treat them. I wonder if any of the parents recognized the true nature of this and why it's so incredibly wrong. Some surely did. It makes me sad. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=208614">My stuff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalmonious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talmonious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/27/02 11:57:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17273.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm in the minority on this subject....</span><hr size=1> I totally agree that it's a double standard and wrong.<br>
<br>
How's this for another double standard: I, being a southerner and proud of my heritage have a big ole confederate flag on the wall of my bedroom.  I share the exact  same opinions about the matter as you folks do but would be considered racist 9 times out of 10 by the Politically Correct extremist wannabes.<br>
<br>
I'm not a racist. I'm proud of my heritage not some believer in oppressing folks.  Double Standards suck.<br>
<br>
As for the laws we have now, COME ON! That junk was long ago that the laws were created for. Sure women still don't make as much as men but it's far from being the discrimination of the past.  Perhaps it's not time for the laws to be repealed but perhaps they should be modified to better fit todays society.<br>
<br>
